<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Free Ham Radio Curriculum — independent open curriculum."
  current="about"
>
  <h1>About Free Ham Radio Curriculum</h1>

  <h2>What this is</h2>
  <p>
    Free Ham Radio Curriculum is a free, open curriculum of workshops and activities that take learners from no
    radio experience toward confident HF operation. Materials include slides, learner handouts,
    trainer guides, and promo copy — built so any experienced Ham can lead a session with minimal
    prep.
  </p>

  <h2>What this is not</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Not a license exam prep course — it complements ARRL and other licensing resources</li>
    <li>Not an online course — these materials are for in-person groups</li>
    <li>Not affiliated with any radio club, league, or vendor</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Independence</h2>
  <p>
    Free Ham Radio Curriculum is an independent project. It is non-partisan and not affiliated with any
    organization except a pending grant application to{' '}
    <a href="https://www.ampr.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer">ARDC</a> (Amateur Radio Digital
    Communications).
  </p>

  <h2>License</h2>
  <p>
    Curriculum materials and this website’s source are published under{' '}
